00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,458
is a small price to pay.

270
00:12:13,541 --> 00:12:15,666
[HARUHI]
Kyon, are you paying attention?

271
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:18,541
Would you be serious here?
This isn't a date, got it?

272
00:12:18,625 --> 00:12:20,250
[KYON]
Yeah, I hear ya.

273
00:12:21,666 --> 00:12:23,125
Look, this isn't fun and games!

274
00:12:23,208 --> 00:12:25,625
You mess around
and I'll kill ya!

275
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:27,833
[KYON] And with those parting
words, Haruhi's team left

276
00:12:27,916 --> 00:12:31,125
to investigate the east side of
the station while Miss Asahina

277
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:34,416
and I were ordered to search the
west side. However...

278
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,583
What should we do?

279
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:37,750
[KYON]
Beats me.

280
00:12:41,125 --> 00:12:42,125
[MIKURU]
This is the first time

281
00:12:42,208 --> 00:12:44,500
I've ever gone for
a walk like this.

282
00:12:44,583 --> 00:12:46,083
By like this, you mean...?

283
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:49,125
Out walking alone with a boy.

284
00:12:49,208 --> 00:12:50,333
Oh!

285
00:12:51,416 --> 00:12:53,125
Come on, I can't believe that.

286
00:12:53,208 --> 00:12:54,958
You're telling me that you've
never gone out on a date

287
00:12:55,041 --> 00:12:56,208
with anyone before?

288
00:12:56,291 --> 00:12:57,625
[MIKURU]
Never.

289
00:12:57,708 --> 00:12:59,166
Hah, you're kidding, right?

290
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:01,458
I mean, don't you have guys
just lining up to ask you out?

291
00:13:01,541 --> 00:13:04,666
Mm. But... I can't do it.

292
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:07,458
You see, I'm not supposed to
go out on dates with anyone.

293
00:13:07,541 --> 00:13:08,750
At least not in this--

294
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:09,791
[gasps]

295
00:13:13,916 --> 00:13:14,916
Kyon.

296
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:18,125
I've gotta favor to ask of you.

297
00:13:18,208 --> 00:13:20,750
[KYON] After a couple of false
starts, Miss Asahina finally

298
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:23,083
started putting her words
into complete sentences

299
00:13:23,166 --> 00:13:24,750
and began to explain.

300
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:27,625
[MIKURU] You might not believe
a word I'm about to say,

301
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:30,958
but the truth is, I'm not
actually from this time plane.

302
00:13:31,041 --> 00:13:33,666
I come from the future.

303
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:36,541
I can't tell you from which
time period or time plane

304
00:13:36,625 --> 00:13:38,041
I come from, though.

305
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:40,625
Telling anything about the
future to anyone from the past

306
00:13:40,708 --> 00:13:43,250
is restricted.
I was told this before

307
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:44,833
I boarded the time machine.

308
00:13:44,916 --> 00:13:48,000
Ah... think of it as being
a lot like animation.

309
00:13:48,083 --> 00:13:50,541
The pictures look like
they're in motion, right?

310
00:13:50,625 --> 00:13:53,875
But it's just a series of still
frames laid out in a sequence.

311
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:57,083
Time is just like that...

312
00:13:57,166 --> 00:13:59,583
Time travelling is moving in a
three-dimensional direction

313
00:13:59,666 --> 00:14:01,541
along the various time planes.

314
00:14:01,625 --> 00:14:04,125
I'm from the future.
That means on this time plane,

315
00:14:04,208 --> 00:14:06,208
I'm sort of like an extra
picture in the middle

316
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:09,750
of one of those flip book
animation things.

317
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:11,416
[KYON]
What is it now?

318
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:14,291
As for me, I'm here because
a large time click

319
00:14:14,375 --> 00:14:16,166
happened three years ago.

320
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:19,041
That's three years ago from
the current time in this plane.

321
00:14:19,125 --> 00:14:20,916
We arrived in the
past to investigate,

322
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,791
and we were surprised
once we got here.

323
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:24,166
No matter how hard we tried,

324
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:27,500
we couldn't go further back
in time from that plane.

325
00:14:27,583 --> 00:14:30,250
The conclusion was that there
had to be a large time gap

326
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:31,833
between the time planes.

327
00:14:31,916 --> 00:14:35,250
It wasn't until recently that we
found the thing that caused it.

328
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:38,750
That is... recently in the
future where I come from.

329
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:40,125
So what is the reason?

330
00:14:40,208 --> 00:14:41,208
Miss Suzumiya.

331
00:14:41,291 --> 00:14:42,583
[KYON]
Not again.

332
00:14:42,666 --> 00:14:45,416
She was at the very center
of the time distortion,

333
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:47,541
and I can't explain any more
of this to you because

334
00:14:47,625 --> 00:14:50,416
it's classified information.
But we are certain that it was

335
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:53,500
Miss Suzumiya who closed
our access to the past.

336
00:14:53,583 --> 00:14:55,916
[KYON] It's hard to believe
that Haruhi would be able

337
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,333
to do something like that.

338
00:14:57,416 --> 00:14:59,708
Believe me, it's a
mystery to us as well.

339
00:14:59,791 --> 00:15:01,458
And Miss Suzumiya doesn't
realize that she's

340
00:15:01,541 --> 00:15:04,708
the cause of the time quake,
either. That's where I come in.

341
00:15:04,791 --> 00:15:07,166
I was sent here to see whether
or not there'll be any new

342
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:09,958
time anomalies occurring
near Miss Suzumiya.

343
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:13,541
I guess... I'm kind
of like a watchdog.

344
00:15:13,625 --> 00:15:15,375
I'll understand if you
don't wanna believe

345
00:15:15,458 --> 00:15:16,791
what I just told you.

346
00:15:16,875 --> 00:15:19,750
No, it's not that, it's just...
why are you telling me?

347
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:22,666
Because you are the one that
Miss Suzumiya has chosen.

348
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:25,291
I can't explain because it's
classified information,

349
00:15:25,375 --> 00:15:27,416
but you are very important
to Miss Suzumiya.

350
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:29,333
There are reasons behind
everything she does.

351
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:32,291
Every time she raises her
hand or takes a step.

352
00:15:32,375 --> 00:15:34,416
What about Nagato
and the new guy?

353
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:37,916
[MIKURU] Oh, well, they're in
very similar positions to me.

354
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,958
I never expected Miss Suzumiya
to get us all together

355
00:15:41,041 --> 00:15:43,000
in such a precise
manner, though.

356
00:15:43,083 --> 00:15:44,666
So that means you
know who or what

357
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:46,291
both of them really are, right?

358
00:15:46,375 --> 00:15:47,333
That's classified.

359
00:15:47,416 --> 00:15:48,666
[gasps]

360
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:50,625
Can you tell me what's
going to happen to Haruhi?

361
00:15:50,708 --> 00:15:52,125
[MIKURU]
That's classified.

362
00:15:52,208 --> 00:15:53,666
Well, if you're
from the future,

363
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:55,500
you already know
what happens, right?

364
00:15:55,583 --> 00:15:57,583
[MIKURU]
That's classified.

365
00:15:57,666 --> 00:16:00,791
Well, then, why don't you just
tell Haruhi all this stuff?

366
00:16:00,875 --> 00:16:02,500
[MIKURU]
That's classified.

367
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,541
I'm sorry, but I'm
not authorized

368
00:16:06,625 --> 00:16:08,125
to say anything
right now.

369
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:10,166
You don't have to believe me.

370
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:13,583
I just wanted you to know
about it, that's all.

371
00:16:13,666 --> 00:16:15,666
[KYON] I just heard the same
thing a couple of days ago,

372
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:17,541
didn't I?

373
00:16:17,625 --> 00:16:20,625
[MIKURU] I'm sorry to dump
all this on you like I did.

374
00:16:20,708 --> 00:16:22,666
Don't apologize, I don't mind.

375
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:25,708
[KYON] So now we've got an
alien and a time traveler.

376
00:16:25,791 --> 00:16:27,291
What's going on here?

377
00:16:27,375 --> 00:16:29,458
If there's anybody out there
who believes in all this stuff,

378
00:16:29,541 --> 00:16:33,125
please, call me.
We'll trade places.

379
00:16:34,125 --> 00:16:34,916
Miss Asahina.

380
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,000
Yes?

381
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,875
You mind if we put
all this on hold?

382
00:16:37,958 --> 00:16:39,750
I mean, is it okay if we
just put aside whether

383
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:42,500
I believe you or not and
just get back to it later?

384
00:16:42,583 --> 00:16:43,708
Sure.

385
00:16:43,791 --> 00:16:45,875
Before we do, can I
ask you one question?

386
00:16:45,958 --> 00:16:47,500
Yes, what is it?

387
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:51,416
If you wouldn't mind, could you
tell me how old you really are?

388
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,375
That's classified.

389
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:55,416
[KYON]
After that little conversation,

390
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:57,041
Haruhi called me on my cell,

391
00:16:57,125 --> 00:16:59,541
and we all got together
again at noon.

392
00:16:59,625 --> 00:17:00,583
Find anything?

393
00:17:00,666 --> 00:17:01,458
[KYON]
Nothing.

394
00:17:01,541 --> 00:17:02,791
Were you guys really looking?

395
00:17:02,875 --> 00:17:04,791
I hope you weren't just
wandering around, Mikuru.

396
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:06,583
Ah! N-No!

397
00:17:06,666 --> 00:17:09,375
What about you?
Did you find anything?

398
00:17:09,458 --> 00:17:11,625
[KYON] While we ate lunch,
Haruhi said she wanted

